# Code One — Project Rules
# This file is loaded into every AI agent's system prompt as persistent context.
# Keep it concise. These are rules, not documentation.

## Project Identity
- Working name: code-one
- Type: Desktop-first modular AI development platform
- Repo: Ghenghis/code-one
- Stack: Electron + React + Monaco + xterm.js + TypeScript + pnpm monorepo

## Architecture Rules
- 7 tiers (0-7) + Tier 4.5 Automation Fabric
- No module may depend on a higher-tier module
- Every major feature lives behind a module boundary
- shared-types is the only cross-cutting dependency

## Development Rules
- Research note before implementation
- ADR before architectural decisions
- Feature branches per subsystem (feat/*, research/*, fix/*)
- Conventional commits with subsystem scope
- No direct pushes to main
- Tests required for all non-trivial code
- Proof of working state before claiming completion

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode
- ESLint + Prettier enforced
- Prefer interfaces over types for public contracts
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- No classes unless state management requires them
- Keep functions small and focused

## Agent Behavior
- Verify before claiming completion
- Use diff preview for file changes
- Narrow scoped commits only
- Do not modify files outside the current milestone scope
- Always check tier boundaries before adding dependencies
